{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "22", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "55", "S": "54"}}, "news": [{"title": "Projects worth \u20b931,000 crore approved under Urban Challenge Fund: MoHUA official", "para": "Projects worth \u20b931,000 crore have been approved under the Urban Challenge Fund within 20-25 days of its guidelines being finalised, said D Thara, additional secretary, Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs. NBFCs account for 44% of the financing for approved projects.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/31000-crore-approved-for-urban-development-through-challenge-fund-mohua/132551040?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-387908/132551040.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "John Abraham buys 100-year-old Bandra bungalow for \u20b984 crore; \u2018no redevelopment plans\u2019", "para": "Actor John Abraham recently bought a historic bungalow in Bandra West for eighty-four crore rupees. This property, built in nineteen twenty-six, was owned by the DeVitre family. Abraham also purchased a Linking Road bungalow in Khar for seventy-five crore rupees last December. Many Bollywood personalities invest heavily in Mumbai real estate for personal and investment reasons. Celebrities often prefer properties in the Bandra to Andheri suburbs.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/john-abraham-invests-84-crore-in-historic-bandra-bungalow-no-redevelopment-plans/132550873?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-40932/132550873.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Redevelopment agreement not a property receipt, so not taxable: ITAT", "para": "Mumbai ITAT ruled agreement registration does not mean property receipt.  Tax cannot be levied on future property rights under anti-abuse provisions.  The tribunal allowed a taxpayer's appeal against a \u20b91.38 crore tax addition.  Registration creates contractual rights, not actual property possession or receipt.  This decision clarifies tax treatment for ongoing redevelopment projects in Mumbai.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/itat-rules-redevelopment-agreements-are-not-taxable-property-receipts/132550795?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-126050/132550795.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}